      "type": "theory",
      "id": "theory_bin_to_dec",
      "title": "Converting Binary to Decimal",
      "content": "Converting from binary to decimal is straightforward: multiply each bit by its position value (power of 2), then add them all up!\n\nHere's the step-by-step method:\n\n1. Write down the binary number\n2. Write the position values below each bit (starting from 1 on the right)\n3. Multiply each bit by its position value\n4. Add all the results together\n\nExample: Convert 1011 to decimal\n\nBinary:    1    0    1    1\nPositions: 8    4    2    1\nCalculate: 1\u00d78  0\u00d74  1\u00d72  1\u00d71\nResults:   8 +  0 +  2 +  1 = 11\n\nSo 1011 in binary equals 11 in decimal!\n\nAnother example: 11010\n\nBinary:    1    1    0    1    0\nPositions: 16   8    4    2    1\nCalculate: 1\u00d716 1\u00d78  0\u00d74  1\u00d72  0\u00d71\nResults:   16 + 8 +  0 +  2 +  0 = 26\n\nPro tip: You only need to add position values where there's a 1. Positions with 0 contribute nothing!"
    },
